article.headline: Lehning helps No. 21 Kansas State get past Colorado
article.linkText: Lehning's triple-double propels K-State to win
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. -- Senior guard Shalee Lehning recorded her first triple-double in Big 12 play in leading Kansas State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today) past Colorado 71-61 Saturday.

      Lehning had 16 points, 11 rebounds and 12 assists as Kansas State (23-6, 10-6) snapped a four-game road losing streak.

      Marlies Gipson led the Wildcats with 21 points.

      Kara Richards scored 19 points for the Buffaloes (11-17, 3-13), and Brittany Spears added 18.

      The game was tied at 37 at halftime after Colorado's Bianca Smith sank three free throws.
